  "text": "Human peers can positively affect learning outcomes, by transferring their knowledge onto the learner, increasing task enjoyment, or allowing for learning-by-teaching [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . One of the advantages of robots over other forms of technology is that they can take up various roles in learning interactions, such as tutors, teaching assistants, and, crucially, peers. Perhaps robot can, similarly to human peers, enhance learning outcomes.",
